name: wheelchair accessible trails
description: Trails designed with flat surfaces, minimal inclines, and no obstacles to accommodate wheelchair users.

name: accessible viewpoints
description: Viewpoints with ramps or flat access, ensuring easy visibility for those with mobility issues.

name: accessible picnic areas
description: Picnic areas with wide, flat surfaces, accessible tables, and easy wheelchair access.

name: accessible shelters
description: Shelters that are easy to access for individuals with mobility challenges, featuring ramps, flat entrances, and accessible pathways.

name: accessible parking
description: Parking spots located close to facilities, with extra space for wheelchair access, and clear markings.

name: wheelchair accessible restrooms
description: Restrooms with wide stalls, handrails, accessible sinks, for wheelchair

name: family restrooms
description: Gender-neutral restrooms with enough space for families, caregivers, and individuals needing assistance.

name: clear signage
description: Clear and easy-to-read signs, good color contrast and symbols.

name: accessible maps
description: Park maps that highlight accessible routes, facilities, and emergency stations, including tactile and braille options.

name: accessible campsites
description: Campsites with hard surfaces, accessible tables, designated accessible sites, and pathways designed for easy access.

name: accessible cabins
description: Cabins with ramps, wide doorways, accessible interiors

name: accessible public transportation
description: Public transportation options that offer wheelchair access and accomodation

name: accessible visitor centers
description: Visitor centers with accessible entrances, ramps, elevators.

name: automatic doors
description: Doors that automatically open

name: tactile maps

name: accessible beach access
description: Paths and ramps that allow wheelchair users to access the beach easily
